{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d17ca193-59c1-490c-a51b-e8f4e66d5d23","content":"You're on **MSTest 3.8.2 / .NET 9.0** — great, you have access to the modern patterns.\n\n### Recommended approach\n\nIn MSTest v3+, use **constructor injection** for `TestContext` and sync setup, and **`[TestInitialize]`** for async setup:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests : IAsyncDisposable, IDisposable\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private HttpClient _client;\n\n    // Constructor: sync init + TestContext injection\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n        _client = new HttpClient();\n    }\n\n    // Async init\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task InitAsync()\n    {\n        await _client.GetAsync(\"https://example.com/warmup\");\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task MyTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Running test...\");\n        // ...\n    }\n\n    // Cleanup\n    public void Dispose() => _client?.Dispose();\n\n    public ValueTask DisposeAsync()\n    {\n        Dispose();\n        return ValueTask.CompletedTask;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **Constructor** — sync init + `TestContext` injection (MSTest 3.x feature)\n- **`[TestInitialize]`** — async init (`async Task` return)\n- **`IDisposable` / `IAsyncDisposable`** — preferred over `[TestCleanup]`\n- The old `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property still works but constructor injection is the modern way","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a319c2a8-d89a-4b02-bb48-1b79ee9bae3c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"They're using MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9.0. In modern MSTest (v3+), the recommended approach is constructor-based initialization rather than `[TestInitialize]`. TestContext can be injected via the constructor. Let me provide the recommended pattern.\n\nKey points for MSTest 3.x:\n- `TestContext` can be injected via constructor (constructor injection)\n- You can use constructors for sync init and `[TestInitialize]` for async init\n- `IAsyncDisposable` / `IDisposable` for cleanup\n- The old property-based `TestContext` still works but constructor injection is preferred in MSTest 3.x","outputTokens":580,"requestId":"0421:100381:2D63A9:360662:69E822A5"},"id":"501794b2-981a-4f47-9e93-5f2bf67d753b","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:21:53.825Z","parentId":"912f445e-b465-4fb0-8e86-d6a673b46ecf"}
